			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Thank you for your answers. 
<br />

<br />
I've solved the problem (although the solution is quite strange). I've noticed when logging to phpMyAdmin that all tables related to phpBB except &quot;phpbb_textual_confirmation&quot; has encoding &quot;latin1_swedish_ci&quot; and only the last one has &quot;cp1251_general_ci&quot;. I've changed the encoding of the table &quot;phpbb_textual_confirmation&quot; to &quot;latin1_swedish_ci&quot; and now it works correctly with cyrillic characters (a bit strange solution, isn't it?).</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
